&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Directorate of Specialised Cancer Services&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term GP CLINCIAL ASSISTANT/&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Breast physician&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; in ONCOLOGY&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are offering an exciting opportunity for GPs, Breast Physicians and other clinicians with relevant experience who wish to develop a specialist interest in the management of Breast Cancer. The post is to support the Specialised Cancer Services Directorate of the Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust. The directorate runs a combination of a full day oncology clinic held in Doncaster or a supporting telephone clinic from Sheffield. The successful applicant will work in partnership with other members of the clinical team including Consultant Oncologists, Junior Doctors, Clinical Nurse Specialists and other Allied Health Professionals. They will be involved in assessing chemotherapy and follow-up patients within breast oncology clinics. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;This a fixed term initially for 6 month post in the first instance to cover a period of maternity leave due to commence on 18 January 2021. Should any further vacancies arise then shortlisted candidates may be considered.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Should candidates experience difficulty in applying for the post please contact the Medical HR Department on telephone number (0114) 2713756 quoting reference number 190-STH-20-216.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sheffield Teaching Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust promotes Equality of opportunity and Diversity within the workplace.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sue Maleham, Assistant Medical HR Manager, Email address: susan.maleham@nhs.net, Telephone number: 0114 2713756&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Informal visits are encouraged and should be arranged through Dr J E Martin, Clinical Director, Oncology on telephone number (0114) 226 5241&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
